        <num>CCP 921</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 3.  EXCEPTIONS
Art. 921.  Exception defined
An exception is a means of defense, other than a denial or avoidance of the demand, used by the defendant, whether in the principal or an incidental action, to retard, dismiss, or defeat the demand brought against him.</p>
        </content>
